---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import Wordmark from "../../components/Wordmark.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — VoiceDrop"
  description="VoiceDrop privacy policy. On-device transcription. No audio or transcripts leave your iPhone."
>
  <Wordmark withMark />

  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="updated">Last updated: 2026-04-18</p>

  <p class="lede">
    VoiceDrop records audio and transcribes it on your device using Apple's
    Neural Engine via the open-source
    <a href="https://github.com/FluidInference/FluidAudio">FluidAudio</a>
    library (Parakeet TDT v3 model from NVIDIA, CC-BY-4.0 license).
    <strong
      >Audio data and transcripts are never transmitted to us or to any third
      party.</strong
    >
  </p>

  <h2>What we store locally</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Transcripts you create</strong>, saved to your device's Documents
      directory. Delete them anytime from the History tab or by deleting the app.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>The speech model file</strong>, cached after a one-time download
      from Hugging Face's public model hub on first use (~600 MB).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Your app settings</strong> (silence detection, auto-copy, language
      mode), stored in <span class="kbd">UserDefaults</span> on your device.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Shared App Group storage</h2>
  <p>
    VoiceDrop's keyboard extension and main app share a small
    <span class="kbd">UserDefaults</span> store (identifier
    <span class="kbd">group.com.ukintvs.voicedrop</span>) to hand off transcribed
    text between processes. Entries have a short time-to-live:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Keyboard insertion text</strong>: 2 minutes, single-consume
      (cleared the moment the keyboard reads it to insert at your cursor).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Deferred pasteboard text</strong>: 10 minutes, cleared after the
      main app writes it to the system pasteboard.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>Both stores are cleared when you uninstall the app.</p>

  <h2>Network activity</h2>
  <p>
    The <strong>only</strong> network request VoiceDrop makes is a one-time
    download of the speech model from
    <span class="kbd">huggingface.co</span> during onboarding or first use. After
    the model is cached, VoiceDrop runs entirely offline.
  </p>
  <p>
    The FluidAudio library also fetches a small Silero VAD model (silence
    detection) from the same source on first use. Same offline-after-cache
    behavior.
  </p>

  <h2>No tracking, no analytics, no third-party SDKs collecting data</h2>
  <p>
    VoiceDrop does not integrate any analytics SDK (Firebase, Segment,
    Amplitude, etc.) and does not send usage data to any server. Apple's
    TestFlight and App Store Connect aggregate crash and performance reports via
    <span class="kbd">MetricKit</span>, delivered to the developer as part of
    the normal iOS app lifecycle; these reports are subject to Apple's privacy
    policy. You can opt out of sharing these reports in
    <strong>Settings → Privacy &amp; Security → Analytics &amp; Improvements</strong
    >
    on your iPhone.
  </p>

  <h2>Data deletion</h2>
  <p>
    Delete the VoiceDrop app to remove all locally stored data. Transcripts, the
    model cache, settings, and App Group storage are all cleared on uninstall.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-party components</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="https://github.com/FluidInference/FluidAudio">FluidAudio</a>
       (MIT) — open-source speech recognition, runs on-device.
    </li>
    <li>OnboardingKit (MIT) — SwiftUI onboarding UI, no data collection.</li>
    <li>Pow (MIT) — SwiftUI animation effects, no data collection.</li>
    <li>
      Parakeet TDT v3 (CC-BY-4.0) — NVIDIA speech model, runs on-device.
    </li>
    <li>Silero VAD (MIT) — silence detection model, runs on-device.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this policy or VoiceDrop's data practices? Email
    <a
      href="mailto:ukint-vs@proton.me?subject=VoiceDrop%20privacy%20question"
      >ukint-vs@proton.me</a
    >.
  </p>
</Base>

<style>
  .updated {
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    font-size: 14px;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-2xl);
  }

  ul {
    padding-left: var(--space-lg);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-md);
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
</style>
